1889[174][175]
August 7, 2015
Airbus A320-200
En route from Boston Logan Airport to Salt Lake City
The plane had to make an emergency landing at the Denver International Airport after a hailstorm at the Nebraska-Colorado border about 120 nm east of Denver severely damaged its windshields and nose cone, impairing visibility through the windshields and disabling the weather radar. Engines were also damaged, and the hail also partially tore the plane's fuselage.
