129 (2017)[176]
July 6, 2017
Boeing 767-300
Over Canadian airspace
Flight 129 from Seattle to Beijing had an altercation mid-flight where a male passenger named Joseph Daniel Hudek attempted to open an emergency exit (which is impossible at that altitude due to the difference in air pressure) and assaulted a flight attendant in the first-class cabin. Several other passengers became involved in the situation in an attempt to subdue Hudek. The flight returned to Seattle without further incident where Hudek was arrested. The flight attendant and one other passenger who tried to subdue the suspect were taken to the hospital for non-life-threatening injuries. Federal charges were filed against Hudek and he may face up to 20 years in prison and fines up to US$250,000.
